    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>passionateinmarketing.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>State Bank of India, the country’s largest bank and the banker to over 21 crore women strengthens its ‘<em>women empowerment’<\/em> mission with the launch of a special training program tailored exclusively for women across its 153 Rural Self Employment Training Institutes (RSETIs). This program that is inaugurated on the occasion of Republic Day is set to benefit approximately 5,200 women candidates. The programme was virtually inaugurated jointly by Shri. Shailesh Kumar Singh, Secretary, (MoRD) and Shri. C. S. Setty, Chairman, SBI. The inauguration ceremony witnessed the presence of SBI’s Managing Director, Shri. Vinay Tonse as well. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.passionateinmarketing.com\/sbi-champions-women-entrepreneurship-launches-skill-development-program-for-5200-women\/\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
