    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>cnbctv18.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In India, women consitute just 14% of entrepreneurs, overseeing 20% of micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs) among 58.5 million enterprises. According to the State of India's Livelihood Report by Access Publications, despite contributing 3.09% to industrial output and employing 10% of workers, the country ranks 57 out of 65 for women's entrepreneurship globally, with only 2.16% of women participating in early-stage entrepreneurial activities. A recent NITI Aayog study reveals that over 99% of Indian MSMEs operate in the micro sector, where more than 99% of women-owned enterprises are single-person micro-businesses, with only 17% employing workers, mostly fewer than 6. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cnbctv18.com\/economy\/gender-disparity-only-14-of-entrepreneurs-in-india-are-women-18823391.htm\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
