    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>business-northeast.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Entrepreneurship Development Institute of India (EDII), in collaboration with Accenture, inaugurated a 26-day <em>Micro Skillpreneurship Development Program<\/em> on Handloom for rural women at Adarshagaon, Chaygaon, Champak Nagar in Kamrup district on September 12. This initiative, led by EDII's North East Regional Office in Guwahati, aims to empower rural women by providing them with essential skills and technical knowledge to start their own businesses. The program focuses on handloom, offering training on Jacquard machines, design development, business management, financial literacy, and marketing strategies. Participants will also gain access to microloans and receive ongoing support to establish individual and group enterprises. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.business-northeast.com\/edii-and-accenture-launch-micro-skillpreneurship-development-program-for-rural-sc-women\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
