    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>timesofindia.indiatimes.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a move to empower women and boost rural entrepreneurship, the Sambalpur district administration has set up three rural industrial parks. The three parks, which aim to provide basic infrastructure with working space to women to process and add value to products, have been set up at Parmanpur under Maneswar block, Tainsar under Kuchinda block and Keseibahal under Bamra block in the district. An official said the rural industrial parks offer facilities such as warehouses, processing plants and packing facilities to support the production and marketing of products. <a href=\"https:\/\/timesofindia.indiatimes.com\/city\/bhubaneswar\/rural-industrial-parks-for-women-entrepreneurs-in-sambalpur\/articleshow\/106364616.cms\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
