    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>upsccolorfullnotes.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Union Cabinet chaired by Prime Minister has approved a new scheme to provide drones to 15,000 Women Self Help Groups (SHGs) across India. As announced, the scheme has an outlay of Rs. 1261 crore for a 2-year duration from 2024-25 to 2025-26. The key objectives of the scheme are to empower women entrepreneurs, infuse advanced technology like drones in the agriculture sector for enhanced efficiency and productivity, and improve crop yields through precise and targeted applications. The drones provided to women SHGs will be rented out to farmers for agriculture purposes like spraying fertilizers and pesticides. <a href=\"https:\/\/upsccolorfullnotes.com\/15000-farming-drones-for-women-shg\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
