    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>indiaeducationdiary.in<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The University Women’s Polytechnic, AMU organized a two-day workshop on Entrepreneur Skills for Women Empowerment in association with the Institution of Engineers India (IEI) Aligarh local centre recently. There were total 150 registrations from students, research scholars and faculty members In the inaugural session the chief guest Prof. Mohammad Altamush Siddiqui, Dean Faculty of Engineering and Technology addressed the participants and the proceedings were released by him. The guest of honor Er. JK Varshney, Honorary Secretary Institution of Engineers India (IEI), Aligarh local centre also deliberated on occasion. Ms Sheeba Kamal Assistant Professor in Applied Science and Humanities section, presented the vote of thanks. Total four technical sessions were conducted in two days. In the first technical session the resource person Dr Jahangir Chauhan, Assistant Professor, Department of Commerce spoke on Women entrepreneurship. <a href=\"https:\/\/indiaeducationdiary.in\/two-day-workshop-on-entrepreneur-skills-for-women-empowerment\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
