    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>theprint.in<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emphasizing the need for women empowerment, Prime Minister Narendra Modi said on Saturday that in today’s new India, the strength of women’s power is reflected from Panchayat Bhawan to Rashtrapati Bhavan, adding that the government is working continuously to create new avenues for women entrepreneurs in the villages. PM Modi addressed the ‘Self Help Group Conference’ in Sheopur on Saturday. He said that the conference of Self Help Groups on Vishwakarma Jayanti is very special in itself. Speaking at the occasion, Prime Minister said, “On this day, it is generally my endeavour that I go to my mother, touch her feet and seek blessings. Today I could not go to her, but lakhs of mothers working hard in tribal areas and villages are blessing me here today. Mothers and sisters are my strength and inspiration.\" <a href=\"https:\/\/theprint.in\/india\/govt-to-create-new-avenues-for-women-entrepreneurs-in-villages-pm-modi\/1132316\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
