    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>news9live.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a bid to support women entrepreneurs to expand their businesses, the Central Government has started 'Mahila e-Haat'. The Mahila e-Haat, established by the Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India under Rashtriya Mahila Kosh (RMK), provides a web-based marketing platform for women entrepreneurs to directly sell their products to their buyers. In a bid to increase the visibility of major PSUs, IRCTC, and nationalised banks like SBI, have given a link to Mahila e-Haat on their websites. The Entrepreneurship Development Institute of India (EDII), recognised as a 'Centre of Excellence' by the central government in the field of skilling ecosystem in the country, has also joined hands with noted corporates to create 10,000 women-led green businesses in 100 districts in 1,000 days. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.news9live.com\/utility\/mahila-e-haat-all-you-need-to-know-about-online-marketing-platform-launched-to-facilitate-women-entrepreneurs-194430\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
