    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>http:\/\/bwpeople.businessworld.in\/<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a revolutionary move, The government of Telangana and The Australian Department of Foreign Affairs came together to promote and reward the women entrepreneurs of both the nations. This partnership known as CyberTech Women Entrepreneurs program, is a platform for women entrepreneurs to provide more access and business resources for the women-led-technology businesses in Australia and India. This move comes under the Australia-India-Bilateral Cyber and Critical Technology Partnership (AICCTP), which is supported by the Australian Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade’s Cyber team. This program will host six women-led Indian start-ups and sis women-led Australian start-ups in the field of cyber security and critical technologies. The program has an objective to support these start-ups in both the nations along with supporting them in their respective markets for three months beyond this program. <a href=\"http:\/\/bwpeople.businessworld.in\/article\/India-And-Australia-Come-Together-To-Push-Female-Tech-Talent-\/09-09-2022-445991\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
