    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>inventiva.co.in<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A 42-year-old lady, like many other Indians, lost her employability as a result of the epidemic. Through a job fulfillment site, the history professor accepted the risk of working as a part-time test invigilator. She has been able to meet her financial objectives for the past year and has started two savings accounts for her daughter’s school.  Since India’s independence in 1947, the economy has seen significant changes. There’s a lot to be proud of in terms of what the country has accomplished in recent decades, including increases in income, growth, literacy, life expectancy, and a slew of other economic metrics. Despite this, women’s involvement in the workforce in India is low and has been falling. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.inventiva.co.in\/trends\/enhancing-womens-employability\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
