    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>krishijagran.com<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The  Centre of Excellence for Social Innovation (CESI) of IIMK, in collaboration with NCW and MyGov.in, will create and implement a collaborative online training programme to foster and grow entrepreneurial capability among women entrepreneurs. The programme will be offered bilingually in English and Malayalam to boost awareness and accessibility, according to a press release issued in Kozhikode on May 10. Aspiring women entrepreneurs may now select between two specific programmes, the Foundation Programme in Entrepreneurship and the Advanced Programme in Entrepreneurship, which are tailored to their present employment and skill sets. Lectures, seminars, entrepreneurial speeches, and major mentorship from diverse subject matter experts are included in the four-month, short-term programmes, which comprise sixty hours of online and interactive learning. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/krishijagran.com\/news\/two-special-programmes-launched-for-women-entrepreneurs-check-application-link-inside\/\" target=\"_blank\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
