    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>News Room Post, January10, 2021.<\/em><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aiming to improve lives of rural women and make them self-reliant, Yogi Government has begun training them in ‘Bud Chip’ method of plantation.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Under the initiative, the sugarcane department will train rural women on the ‘Bud Chip’ technology of sugarcane plantation. Also, this method of plantation has been proved to facilitate bulk and quick multiplication of seeds, thereby being stamped more economical and convenient than the traditional method of planting. Hence this is a win-win move for all.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/newsroompost.com\/india\/bud-chip-plantation-yogi-govt-training-rural-women-to-become-self-reliant\/571006.html\">Read more..<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
