    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Livemint.com&nbsp; 30 December, 2020<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The year 2020 was unexpected, unprecedented for the start-up ecosystem in India. The impact of the pandemic and the 70-day lockdown was varied – many startups had a tough time and 15% of India’s 40,000 startups finally had to close down. Interestingly, it has also been highlighted by sheer resilience and reinvention; and for many digital and digitally enabled startups, it was marked by exceptional growth. In fact, startups that survive this crisis will have a larger opportunity in digital economy.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.livemint.com\/opinion\/columns\/2021-to-mark-a-new-era-for-the-indian-startup-ecosystem-11609258202561.html\">Read more….<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
