    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/moneycontrol.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">moneycontrol.com<\/a>&nbsp; May 9, 2020<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Economics has ground to a halt by COVID-19. The way the unprecedented COVID-19 pandemic has impacted the world cannot be imagined.<br>Governments are in a fix, globally and businesses are shaken up and it has dented social and economic systems that focus on corporate profit<br>and it has hit defence expenditure over health, education and social welfare too.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The coronavirus pandemic of 2020 will be a landmark in history for the global lockdowns.&nbsp; And, in India micro, small and medium enterprises<br>(MSMEs) will be the worst hit.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read here how five women entrepreneurs in India as they share their experiences. What is the real impact?  There is loss, but could there<br>be opportunities too?<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/bit.ly\/2SU4FWI\">https:\/\/bit.ly\/2SU4FWI<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
