    "post_content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>NDTV (Press Trust of India)&nbsp; April 4, 2020<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The lockdown is on for sure, but a new initiative has been launched for women. Now women can report domestic violence cases.&nbsp;Women Entrepreneurs For Transformation Foundation launched a subtle and effective initiative called \"Red Dot\". Red is really an eye-catching colour and under this initiative, people can identify a domestic violence victim by seeing a red dot on her palm and can then inform NGOs or authorities.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Incidentally, domestic abuse, which is definitely a crime, has seen a sudden spike ever since the lockdown was imposed in India, following the unprecedented coronavirus outbreak. During this lockdown, crime has had a sudden surge. This has impacted the victims of domestic violence, who suddenly find themselves trapped in their homes with their abusers.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many women have been put into this pathetic state of affairs, and they are either unable or too afraid to call the police to get help to move out.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/bit.ly\/2KIvxo0\">https:\/\/bit.ly\/2KIvxo0<\/a><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
