    "post_content": "The MSME Chamber of Commerce and Industry of India (CCII), in association with the Ministry of MSME, recently presented Anisha Sharma of Hamirpur district in Himachal Pradesh, a national award for entrepreneurship. Anisha is a chartered accountant from Bara village near Bijhari in the district, as well as the executive director of IDS Omni Solutions (P) Ltd.\n\nThe committees had organised a three-day conference at Vigyan Bhawan in New Delhi from Feburary 2. During it, Anisha was conferred the award of “Women Entrepreneur of the Year 2020” on sustainability.\n\nMore than 70 domain specialists and 50 startups from countries like Japan, Germany, Australia, and India, attended the event.\n\nAnisha accepted the award stating that IDS Omni Solutions had been incorporated in 2012 and had branches in Chandigarh and Pune. The company is a BPO dealing in several data entry and data mining projects, and was also awarded the “India 5000 Best MSME Awards for Quality and Excellence” in 2017, for its robust growth curve, statutory compliances, and good work practices. She attributed the success of the company to the hardworking team members and family support, which helped earn it the trust and goodwill of clients.",
